<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-11-16T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-11-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="800" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/908a: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-16T19:00:00-05:00">November 16, 1938—7
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>707. For Rublee. Department’s 705, November 16, noon, and your 1320 November
                        16, 4 p.m.<note n="55" xml:id="d800fn55">Latter not printed.</note> In view
                        of the announcement to the press, <pb facs="0835" n="827" xml:id="pg_827"/>
                        we suggest that the meeting be called for November 28 or 29. We also suggest
                        that both the Brazilian and the Argentine be invited to attend.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>